sentence: The war cry for justice was all over - Much to the chagrin of the authorities.
Japanese: 正義の戦争泣きは、当局の悔い改めに大いにあった。
backtrans: The war crying in justice was great for the repentance of the authorities.

sentence: The regime's decision adumbrates the underlying agenda.
Japanese: 政権の決定は、基礎となる議題を欺く。
backtrans: The decision of the administration deceures the underlying agenda.

sentence: The community was anxious over the passing of the much needed reforms.
Japanese: コミュニティは、多くの必要な改革を通過することに心配していました。
backtrans: The community was worried about passing many necessary reforms.

sentence: The think tank  published a paper outlining their apology of capital punishment.
Japanese: Think Tankは、首都罰の謝罪を概説する論文を発表しました。
backtrans: Think Tank announced a dissertation outlines the apology of the capital punishment.

sentence: Aught was left of the petition's validity
Japanese: AUGHTは請願の妥当性の左にありました
backtrans: AUGHT was on the left of the validity of the petition

sentence: The President exhorted his ministers to buckle up as key opposition support for his economic plan was about to buckle.
Japanese: 彼の経済計画の主な反対のサポートが座屈しようとしているので、大統領は彼の閣僚を座屈立させた。
backtrans: As the main opposite support of his economic plan is trying to buckle, the president sows his ministers.

sentence: The voters were chuffed to see the bill passed.
Japanese: 有権者は紙幣が渡されたのを見るためにかわいいです。
backtrans: Voters are cute to see banknotes passed.

sentence: The lawyer's discursive narration swayed the jury.
Japanese: 弁護士の聴覚的なナレーションは陪審員を揺れました。
彼の裁判所は暴力を行った！

sentence: The EU block opposed an eventual imposition of anti-dumping measures.
Japanese: EUブロックは、ダンピング対策対策の最終的な課題に反対した。
backtrans: The EU block opposed the final challenge of damping measures.

sentence: A fulsome eulogy was delivered by the sly counsel.
Japanese: Fulsome EulogyがSly Counselによって提供されました。
backtrans: FULSOME EULOGY was provided by Sly Counsel.

sentence: The gig-economy agency decided to garnish the refunds!
Japanese: ギグ経済機関は払い戻しを飾ることにしました！

sentence: Members of the anti-theocratic revolutionary movement overthrew the peers in power!
Japanese: 抗Teolocratic革命的な運動のメンバーは、パワーのピアを覆い隠しました！
backtrans: Anti-Teolocratic Revolutionary Members Hide Power Peer!

sentence: The traitors disappointingly decided to fight with the colonialists.
Japanese: 裏切り者は、植民地派と戦うことに失望しています。
backtrans: The trailer is disappointed to fight colonial schools.
